---
description: Enforce Nuxt performance defaults and image/link loading rules when editing Nuxt app files.
globs: **/*.vue, **/*.ts, nuxt.config.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

- Default rendering strategy for marketing pages is SSG/static prerender; exceptions require explicit justification.
- Never use raw `img` tags for app content; use `NuxtImg`/`NuxtPicture`.
- Always set image `width` and `height` to prevent CLS.
- Above-the-fold/hero images: use eager loading with high fetch priority.
- Below-the-fold images: use lazy loading and responsive `sizes`.
- Use `NuxtLink` for internal navigation instead of raw internal `<a href>`.

- 🚩 SSR chosen for marketing pages without clear exception case.
- 🚩 Raw `<img>` used where `NuxtImg`/`NuxtPicture` is expected.
- 🚩 Image missing explicit dimensions.
- 🚩 Hero image incorrectly lazy-loaded.
- 🚩 Internal route uses `<a href>` instead of `NuxtLink`.
- 🚩 Third-party script embedded as raw `<script>` instead of deferred strategy.

See `.cursor/skills/nuxt-performance/SKILL.md` for full implementation detail.
